My Writing Journal Begins

With today, my writing journal begins. Today, I would like to talk about the education system in Turkey.

First of all, the education system in Turkey is different from many other countries in the world. It follows a 12-year structure: 4 years of primary school, 4 years of middle school, and 4 years of high school.

University education in Turkey is optional, as it is in many other countries. However, if a student wants to achieve success through intelligence and hard work, attending a good university is very important.

Getting into university is difficult, but graduating can also be challenging. There are many different majors, and students must choose carefully because it can affect their future careers.

I am currently an 11th-grade student, and unlike many others, I have already started thinking about my university plans. I am determined to succeed.

After university, working life begins. However, job opportunities can be competitive, so students need to do their best during their education.

In Turkey, there are two important exams before university: LGS and YKS. LGS is taken at the end of middle school, and YKS is the university entrance exam.

Overall, the education system in Turkey is challenging, but with hard work and determination, students can succeed.

That is it for today. Thank you for reading.
